-- Bank of China H1 profit up 11.2 pct, meets forecasts
-- 
-- Tue Aug 19, 2014 04:39AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG/SHANGHAI, Aug 19 (Reuters) - Bank of China (BoC) <601988.SS> <3988.HK>, the country's fourth-largest lender by market value, reported an 11.2 percent rise in first half net profit, in line with estimates, as net interest margin held steady.

BoC on Tuesday posted a net profit of 89.7 billion yuan ($14.61 billion) for the January-June period. A Reuters poll of analysts had forecast a net profit of 90.2 billion yuan for the period. BoC's non-performing loan ratio increased slightly to 1.02 percent at end-June compared to 0.98 percent at end-March.